<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9804> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9804" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/16> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 223" ;
	dprr:hasID 9804 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1199> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1199" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap.; Act. Tr. (both names entire); Liv. 30.44.1; Val. Max. 6.5.1, on Lutatius; Eutrop. 2.28; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd. (Torquato et Catone), so also Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.11.6; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.17, and 18; see Degrassi 42f., 117, 438f. The two Consuls subdued the so-called Faliscan revolt and celebrated triumphs De Falisceis (<i>Act. Tr.,</i> Degrassi 76f., 549; Val. Max. 6.5.1; Eutrop. 2.28; Zon. 8.17; cf. Polyb. 1.65.1; Liv. Per. 20; Oros. 4.11.5-10; cf. on Lutatius, Grueber, CRRBM 2.297; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.161f.). Lutatius also went to Sicily, probably early in the year (see dates in Act. Tr.), to assist his brother in making peace with the Carthaginians and in organizing the new territory in Sicily (Zon. 8.17; cf. Polyb. 1.62-64; Val. Max. 1.3.1)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1199 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1190> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1190" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Vell. 1.14.8; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 42f., 117, 436f. Fighting continued around Mt. Eryx (Polyb. 1.58.1-6; cf. Zon. 8.16). Brundisium and Fregenae were founded this year (Vell. 1.14.8, on Brundisium; cf. Liv. Per. 19)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1190 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1184> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1184" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire, but Manlius' cognomen is spelled ATEIC); cf. Liv. Per. 19. See Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f." ;
	dprr:hasID 1184 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10146> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10146" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Falisceis. MRR I.219, Itgenshorst no. 144, Rich no. 143." ;
	dprr:hasID 10146 .
